The LOD of the Cu-CDs-Fe3+ system for AA is calculated to be 6 nM, which is lower than that of Cu-CDs. Compared with other methods, our established method provides comparable or higher linearity ranges and detection limits (Table 2
                        ). The absorption spectrum of the Cu-CDs-Fe3+-AA overlaps with the excitation band of Cu-CDs-Fe3+, and the average fluorescence lifetime of the Cu-CDs-Fe3+ and Cu-CDs-Fe3+-AA is measured to be 3.86 ns and 4.47 ns, respectively (Fig. 5d). Therefore, the mechanism of the observed fluorescence performance should be regulated to the IFE. Therefore, the two systems of direct detection and “on-off-on” detection to identify AA can effectively achieve selective detection of AA. This strategy provides a new idea for the future development of AA sensors. In addition, the fitting details of multi-exponential decay curves of Cu-CDs, Cu-CDs-Fe3+, Cu-CDs-AA and Cu-CDs-Fe3+-AA solutions (τ) have been listed in Table 3
                        .
